title: Trump slaps new tariffs on foreign products made with steel, aluminum
text: President Trump cited national security concerns as he expanded his trademark tariffs to cover things like auto parts, nails, staples and electrical wires. The decision to expand the tariffs came about two years after the first round of tariffs on the imports of raw steel and aluminum, and less than two weeks after Trump signed.
